Document: TextLine
Path: godot/classes/class_textline.rst
Summary: This section describes the properties available for configuring a TextLine object, including text alignment, direction, clipping behavior, and character preservation.

Property Descriptions

*   **alignment** (HorizontalAlignment): Sets text alignment within the line as if the line was horizontal. Default: 0.
    *   Method: set_horizontal_alignment(value: HorizontalAlignment)
    *   Method: get_horizontal_alignment()
*   **direction** (Direction): Text writing direction. Default: 0.
    *   Method: set_direction(value: Direction)
    *   Method: get_direction()
*   **ellipsis_char** (String): Ellipsis character used for text clipping. Default: "…".
    *   Method: set_ellipsis_char(value: String)
    *   Method: get_ellipsis_char()
*   **flags** (bitfield[JustificationFlag]): Line alignment rules. For more info see TextServer. Default: 3.
    *   Method: set_flags(value: bitfield[JustificationFlag])
    *   Method: get_flags()
*   **orientation** (Orientation): Text orientation. Default: 0.
    *   Method: set_orientation(value: Orientation)
    *   Method: get_orientation()
*   **preserve_control** (bool): If set to true text will display control characters. Default: false.
    *   Method: set_preserve_control(value: bool)
    *   Method: get_preserve_control()
*   **preserve_invalid** (bool): If set to true text will display invalid characters. Default: true.
    *   Method: set_preserve_invalid(value: bool)
    *   Method: get_preserve_invalid()
*   **text_overrun_behavior** (OverrunBehavior): The clipping behavior when the text exceeds the text line's set width. Default: 3.
    *   Method: set_text_overrun_behavior(value: OverrunBehavior)
    *   Method: get_text_overrun_behavior()
*   **width** (float): Text line width. Default: -1.0.
    *   Method: set_width(value: float)
    *   Method: get_width()
